"adj. 胃的，胃部的 【英】 adj. 胃的，胃部的(of , in, or near the stomach) 【例】 When I smell good food, my gastric juices begin to flow. adj. 胃的, 胃部的(of, in, or near the stomach) 【根】gastr胃 【记】gas胃胀气, tric = trick(n 诡计)－gas在stomach里有trick－胃胀气－胃的 【参】gastritis(n 胃炎); gastrology(n 胃病学; 美食学); 【记】gast- 胃的 + 音：吃；gas 气，吃东西经常会感到肚子涨气，胃里有气 gastric (adj.)  1650s, with -ic + Greek gaster (genitive gastros) ""stomach,"" by dissimilation from *graster, literally ""eater, devourer,"" from gran ""to gnaw, eat,"" from PIE root *gras- ""to devour"" (cognates: Greek grastis ""green fodder,"" Latin gramen ""fodder, grass,"" Old English cærse ""cress"")."
